From: Keel <ci@keel.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH 0003/0006] keel: ui: hide Rewards/Wallet/Leo toolbar surfaces

Belt-and-suspenders for the managed policies — even if a Keel install ends up
with a stale or missing policy file, the toolbar buttons for Rewards, Wallet,
and Leo AI should never render. This patch turns the three `ShouldShow*Button`
helpers into hard-`false` returns inside the Brave toolbar view.

No effect on the underlying services (we don't disable them here — the
managed-policy keys do that). This is purely visual suppression so the
"hide it from the UI and document the limitation" half of the spec is
honored when policy enforcement fails.

---
 brave/browser/ui/views/toolbar/brave_toolbar_view.cc | 21 ++++++---------------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)

diff --git a/brave/browser/ui/views/toolbar/brave_toolbar_view.cc b/brave/browser/ui/views/toolbar/brave_toolbar_view.cc
--- a/brave/browser/ui/views/toolbar/brave_toolbar_view.cc
+++ b/brave/browser/ui/views/toolbar/brave_toolbar_view.cc
@@
 bool BraveToolbarView::ShouldShowRewardsButton() {
-  return brave_rewards::util::IsRewardsEnabled(profile_);
+  return false;  // keel: never show
 }

 bool BraveToolbarView::ShouldShowWalletButton() {
-  return profile_->GetPrefs()->GetBoolean(kBraveWalletShowInToolbar);
+  return false;  // keel: never show
 }

 bool BraveToolbarView::ShouldShowAIChatButton() {
-  return ai_chat::features::IsAIChatEnabled() &&
-         profile_->GetPrefs()->GetBoolean(kShowAIChatButton);
+  return false;  // keel: never show
 }
